#
# USBGuard rules — LAB-OP baseline (safe, reviewable)
#
# Learned model:
# - Existing LAB-OP hosts keep rules in /etc/usbguard/rules.conf (root-only).
# - Allowlist is device-specific; keep suggestions commented until confirmed.
#
# Policy:
# - Prefer "generate-policy" on the host and then review, instead of guessing device IDs.
# - Keep any real device IDs / hashes in a private overlay under docs/private/homelab/.
#

# --- Suggestions (comment-only; "uncomment to activate") ---
#
# 1) Start from an on-host snapshot (recommended):
#    sudo usbguard generate-policy > /etc/usbguard/rules.conf
#    sudo systemctl restart usbguard
#
# 2) If you have stable, hardwired devices (keyboards, receivers, hubs), allow them by id/name/port.
#
# Examples (do NOT trust blindly; replace placeholders with real values from your host):
#
# allow id 046d:c542 name "Wireless Receiver" with-interface 03:01:02
# allow id 1a2c:0b2a name "USB Keyboard" with-interface { 03:01:01 03:00:00 }
#
# 3) Deny everything else explicitly if you want strict mode:
# deny with-interface *
#
# Keep this file short; large allowlists belong in a private overlay.

